        The position of the liquid water region would likely move away from the sun. This is because a blur star of the same size would be hotter than the sun, and hence the current liquid water region will have planets with surface temperature above 100 degrees celcius. However, temperature is lower further away from the sun, so there will be a region further away from the sun where all planets have a surface temperature between 0 and 100 degrees celcius.
