8.
    a.
        transverse: perpendicular to the axis of travel of the wave;
        longitudinal: parallel to the axis of travel of the wave.
    b?
        The Doppler effect causes the frequency of sound detected by whale B to increase because whale A swims towards whale B. This is because as whale A swims towards whale B, the position from which it emits a sound is moving closer towards whale B. Consequently, the wavelength of the sound decreases. Since frequency = speed / wavelength, since wavelength decreases and the speed of the wave remains the same, frequency must increase.
    c.
        5.7 * 10^(-7) * 3 * 10^(8) = 171 Hz
